📊 Metrics
List all available metrics  
Shows what metrics are being collected for a service.
aws cloudwatch list-metrics --namespace AWS/EC2

Get metric statistics  
Retrieves data points (like average CPU usage) for a given time range.
aws cloudwatch get-metric-statistics \
  --metric-name CPUUtilization \
  --namespace AWS/EC2 \
  --start-time 2026-06-17T00:00:00Z \
  --end-time 2026-06-17T23:59:59Z \
  --period 300 \
  --statistics Average \
  --region ap-south-1

Put custom metric data  
Push your own application metrics into CloudWatch.
aws cloudwatch put-metric-data \
  --metric-name PageLoadTime \
  --namespace MyApp \
  --value 2.5 \
  --unit Seconds

🔔 Alarms
Create an alarm  
Triggers when CPU > 80% for 2 evaluation periods.
aws cloudwatch put-metric-alarm \
  --alarm-name HighCPU \
  --metric-name CPUUtilization \
  --namespace AWS/EC2 \
  --statistic Average \
  --period 300 \
  --threshold 80 \
  --comparison-operator GreaterThanThreshold \
  --dimensions Name=InstanceId,Value=i-1234567890abcdef0 \
  --evaluation-periods 2 \
  --alarm-actions arn:aws:sns:ap-south-1:123456789012:NotifyMe \
  --unit Percent

Describe alarms
aws cloudwatch describe-alarms

Delete an alarm
aws cloudwatch delete-alarms --alarm-names HighCPU

Disable alarm actions
aws cloudwatch disable-alarm-actions --alarm-names HighCPU

Enable alarm actions
aws cloudwatch enable-alarm-actions --alarm-names HighCPU

📜 Logs
Create a log group
aws logs create-log-group --log-group-name MyAppLogs

Create a log stream
aws logs create-log-stream --log-group-name MyAppLogs --log-stream-name Stream1

Put log events
aws logs put-log-events \
  --log-group-name MyAppLogs \
  --log-stream-name Stream1 \
  --log-events file://events.json

Get log events
aws logs get-log-events --log-group-name MyAppLogs --log-stream-name Stream1

Delete a log group
aws logs delete-log-group --log-group-name MyAppLogs

🧠 Logs Insights
Start a query
aws logs start-query \
  --log-group-name MyAppLogs \
  --start-time 1623900000 \
  --end-time 1623986400 \
  --query-string "fields @timestamp, @message | sort @timestamp desc | limit 20"

Get query results
aws logs get-query-results --query-id <query-id>

🧩 Dashboards
List dashboards
aws cloudwatch list-dashboards
Get a dashboard
aws cloudwatch get-dashboard --dashboard-name MyDashboard
Put (create/update) a dashboard
aws cloudwatch put-dashboard \
  --dashboard-name MyDashboard \
  --dashboard-body file://dashboard.json
Delete dashboards
aws cloudwatch delete-dashboards --dashboard-names MyDashboard

⚙️ Events
List rules
aws events list-rules
Put a rule (scheduled event)
aws events put-rule --name EC2StopRule --schedule-expression "rate(5 minutes)"
Put targets for a rule
aws events put-targets --rule EC2StopRule --targets file://targets.json
Delete a rule
aws events delete-rule --name EC2StopRule
